description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREVIOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a qualified Specialist Clinical Physiologist (Neurophysiology ) to join our expanding team. This post is also open to newly qualified clinical physiologists who are looking to expand their skill set. Further training is supported where appropriate.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who likes responsibility, has practical experience across a range of tests and who wants the opportunity to enhance their skills and knowledgebase through further training and experience. You will meet patients from all age ranges and all abilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be enthusiastic, a team player, able to take ownership and also work independently where appropriate. This is great opportunity for you to expand your skill set and also become involved with a wide range of tests including HVT and NCVs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Luton &amp; Dunstable Hospital has recently joined up with Bedford Hospital and this gives Neurophysiology the opportunity to expand and provide the service across both sites in the near future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to find out more about the post or about the future developments in Neurophysiology here at the L&amp;D call the department on 01582 497069 and ask to speak to Christine Rollins – Professional Service Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We encourage all potential applicants to make contact prior to submission of an application form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Christine Rollins&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Professional Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address christine.rollins@ldh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01582 497069&lt;/p&gt;
